name: Winamp Equalizer Presets File
summary: Learn about .Q1 files and view a list of programs that open them.

windows.name: Open over 400 file formats with File Viewer Plus.Free Download

content: Winamp includes a Q1 named Winamp.q1 file that contains several EQ presets. Examples include Classic, Club, Dance, Pop, Rock, etc. When you create a custom preset, it is added to the list of presets saved in the default Q1 file.

You can save custom EQ settings by selecting Options → Equalizer → Save Preset → Preset... from the Winamp menu bar. You can load a specific EQ preset from a Q1 file by selecting Options → Equalizer → Load Preset → Preset....
The default location of the Q1 file is: C:\​Users\​Administrator\​AppData\​Roaming\​Winamp

description: Library of equalizer (EQ) settings created by Winamp, an audio playback application; contains multiple presets for different EQ settings, identified by name.
